Setup required:
Core network:
netstat -an | grep 1234
netstat -an | grep 5000
UE:
netstat -an | grep 1234
RAN:
netstat -an | grep 5000
IP Camera setup:
firefox 192.168.1.100 &
1. IP Camera Streaming (RTSP)
The IP camera exposes its RTSP media stream at:
rtsp://Admin:Admin123@192.168.1.100/axis-media/media.amp

This URL is verified using:
  ffplay rtsp://Admin:Admin123@192.168.1.100/axis-media/media.amp
2. Sender: Transmitting Stream via UDP
The sender encodes RTSP stream and forwards it over UDP for transport across the core network:
ffplay -fflags nobuffer -flags low_delay udp://@:1234
3. Receiver: Playing UDP Stream
On the receiver side, the incoming stream is played with:
   ffplay -fflags nobuffer -flags low_delay udp://@:5000
 4. Core Network
ffmpeg -rtsp_transport tcp -i rtsp://Admin:Admin123@192.168.1.100/axis-media/media.amp \
  -c:v libx264 -preset veryfast -tune zerolatency -b:v 3M -c:a aac \
  -f mpegts udp://192.168.1.12:1234 \
  -c:v libx264 -preset veryfast -tune zerolatency -b:v 3M -c:a aac \
  -f mpegts udp://192.168.1.10:5000
5. Common Issues and Fixes
• Address already in use → Caused by multiple ffplay instances binding to the same port.
  To resolve:
      pkill -9 ffplay

• 401 Unauthorized → Wrong IP camera username/password.

• No video → Ensure UPF rules allow UDP forwarding.


